  <refnamediv>
    <refname>&dhcmd;</refname>

    <refpurpose>Convert format of GLAME persistant storage files</refpurpose>
  </refnamediv>
  <refsynopsisdiv>
    <cmdsynopsis>
	&dhcmd;

      <arg><replaceable>swapfile</replaceable></arg> 
    </cmdsynopsis>
  </refsynopsisdiv>
  <refsect1>
    <title>DESCRIPTION</title>

    <para>The <command>glame</command> audio editor keeps all project data
          on disk in a internal representation, called the
	  swapfile. The format of this swapfile changed between
	  the 0.4, and the 0.6 series of Glame. &dhcmd; lets you convert an
	  0.4 swapfile to 0.6 format and vice versa. It will autodetect
	  which format is currently present and always convert to the other
	  one.

  </refsect1>
  <refsect1>
    <title>OPTIONS</title>

    <variablelist>
      <varlistentry>
        <term><replaceable>swapfile</replaceable>
        </term>
        <listitem>
          <para>File (directory actually) that acts as Glame's backing store.
          </para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
    </variablelist>
  </refsect1>
  <refsect1>
    <title>SEE ALSO</title>

    <para><command>glame</command> (1), <command>cglame</command> (1).</para>

  </refsect1>
